cs.NI, cs.COMM, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the new generation of computer and communication networks, specifically ATM technology, which is a networking protocol. 
2. cs.COMM (Communication and Information Theory) - The paper focuses on traffic management in communication networks, specifically in ATM networks. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the integration of voice, video, and data on the same network, which involves distributed computing. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the latest traffic management technology in ATM networks, which involves control systems. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the integration of voice, video, and data on the same network, which involves multimedia.
